The new National Youth Service Corps (NYSC), Katsina State Coordinator, Hajiya Aisha Mohammed has assumed the mantle of leadership of the scheme in the state. The outgoing state Coordinator, Alhaji Ahidjo Yahaya, while speaking at a brief handing over ceremony at the NYSC Secretariat in Katsina on Tuesday, thanked the staff for their cooperation, dedication and hard work. Ahidjo urged the staff to extend similar cooperation to the new Coordinator to enable her to succeed in the task ahead. -Advertisement- The outgoing Coordinator described the new state coordinator, Hajiya Aisha Mohammad as an experienced and professional officer who rose through the ranks as well as a good person. He, therefore, solicited their support for the new state coordinator to record better achievements for the scheme in the state. Hajiya Aisha Mohammad, the new state NYSC Coordinator, in her remarks said she was happy coming to katsina, urging the staff to come up with ideas to move the scheme to greater heights. She also advised the staff to guide against gossip and slandering as the Almighty Allah frowns at such behaviours, rather they should unite and work together to improve the scheme services in the state. Hajiya Aisha, however, hoped that the staff would extend similar gestures to her to enable her to attain her desired goals more than her predecessor. POLL She promised to make the welfare of Corps members and staff her topmost priority to ensure cordiality unity and peace amongst all.